1-1500+).** Key sections:\\n\\n#### `hasTTY()` (lines 33-58)\\n\\n```go\\nfunc hasTTY() bool {\\n    if v := os.Getenv(\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"); v != \\\"\\\" {\\n        return v == \\\"1\\\"\\n    }\\n    // ... Gemini CLI check ...\\n    tty, err := os.OpenFile(\\\"/dev/tty\\\", os.O_RDWR, 0)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return false\\n    }\\n    _ = tty.Close()\\n    return true\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**`ENTIRE_TEST_TTY` behavior:**\\n- `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1` -- `hasTTY()` returns `true` (simulates human with TTY)\\n- `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` -- `hasTTY()` returns `false` (simulates agent with no TTY)\\n- Not set -- falls through to real `/dev/tty` check\\n\\n**Impact on `PrepareCommitMsg`** (lines 295-470):\\n- When `!hasTTY()` (line 352): if any session is ACTIVE, the fast path `addTrailerForAgentCommit` is taken, which generates a checkpoint ID and adds the trailer directly -- **no content detection, no interactive prompt**\\n- When `hasTTY()`: the full flow runs -- `filterSessionsWithNewContent`, content detection, interactive TTY prompt for `-m` commits, comment-based trailer for editor commits\\n\\n**`askConfirmTTY`** (lines 75-137): When `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY` is set (any value), it immediately returns the default result without trying to read from TTY. This is critical for tests -- setting `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1` makes `hasTTY()` return true, but `askConfirmTTY` still returns the default (no actual TTY I/O).\\n\\n#### `PrepareCommitMsg` (lines 295-470)\\n\\nFlow:\\n1. Skip if git sequence operation (rebase/cherry-pick/revert)\\n2. Skip for merge/squash sources\\n3. Handle amend (`source=\\\"commit\\\"`) separately\\n4. Open repo, find sessions for worktree\\n5. Fast path: `!hasTTY()` + ACTIVE session -> `addTrailerForAgentCommit`\\n6. Filter sessions with new content\\n7. Generate checkpoint ID\\n8. For `source=\\\"message\\\"` (git commit -m): check `commit_linking` setting, may prompt via TTY\\n9. For default (editor): add trailer with explanatory comment\\n\\n#### `PostCommit` (lines 705-813)\\n\\nFlow:\\n1. Open repo, get HEAD commit\\n2. Parse `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer from commit message -- if not found, only update BaseCommit\\n3. Find sessions for worktree\\n4. Build `TransitionContext` (checks rebase)\\n5. Pre-resolve headTree, parentTree, committedFileSet\\n6. For each session: call `postCommitProcessSession`\\n7. Clean up shadow branches\\n\\n#### `postCommitProcessSession` (lines 818-962)\\n\\nPer-session:\\n1. Resolve shadow branch ref and tree\\n2. Check for new content (ACTIVE always true; others check transcript)\\n3. Capture `filesTouchedBefore` (may extract from live transcript for ACTIVE)\\n4. Create `postCommitActionHandler` with all resolved git objects\\n5. Call `TransitionAndLog(ctx, state, EventGitCommit, transitionCtx, handler)`\\n6. If condensed + ACTIVE: record checkpoint ID in `TurnCheckpointIDs`\\n7. Carry-forward remaining files to new shadow branch\\n8. Save updated state\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`\\n\\n**Full content provided above (256 lines).**\\n\\nKey methods on `ManualCommitStrategy`:\\n- **`loadSessionState`** -- delegates to `StateStore.Load()`\\n- **`saveSessionState`** -- delegates to `StateStore.Save()`\\n- **`clearSessionState`** -- delegates to `StateStore.Clear()`\\n- **`listAllSessionStates`** -- lists all sessions, filters out orphans (shadow branch gone + not active + no LastCheckpointID)\\n- **`findSessionsForWorktree`** -- filters by `WorktreePath`\\n- **`initializeSession`** -- creates new `SessionState` with HEAD hash, worktree path, worktree ID, untracked files, TurnID, and saves it\\n- **`getStateStore`** (in `manual_commit.go`) -- lazy init via `sync.Once`, calls `session.NewStateStore(ctx)` which resolves `.git/entire-sessions/` via `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`\\n\\n**Full content provided above (446 lines).**\\n\\n#### `State` struct (lines 33-143)\\n\\nKey fields relevant to benchmarks:\\n- `SessionID string` -- unique session identifier\\n- `BaseCommit string` -- current shadow branch base (HEAD when session starts)\\n- `WorktreePath string` -- absolute path to worktree root\\n- `WorktreeID string` -- internal git worktree identifier\\n- `Phase Phase` -- lifecycle stage (active/idle/ended)\\n- `StepCount int` -- number of checkpoints (JSON: `checkpoint_count`)\\n- `FilesTouched []string` -- files modified/created/deleted\\n- `LastCheckpointID id.CheckpointID` -- from most recent condensation\\n- `AgentType agent.AgentType` -- agent name\\n- `TurnCheckpointIDs []string` -- checkpoint IDs condensed during current turn\\n- `CheckpointTranscriptStart int` -- transcript line offset for current checkpoint cycle\\n\\n#### `StateStore` (lines 220-384)\\n\\n- **`NewStateStore(ctx)`** -- creates store at `.git/entire-sessions/` (via `getGitCommonDir`)\\n- **`NewStateStoreWithDir(stateDir)`** -- testing constructor with custom dir\\n- **`Load(ctx, sessionID)`** -- reads `<stateDir>/<session-id>.json`, returns `(nil, nil)` if not found or stale\\n- **`Save(ctx, state)`** -- atomic write (write to `.tmp`, rename)\\n- **`Clear(ctx, sessionID)`** -- removes the state file\\n- **`List(ctx)`** -- reads all `.json` files in stateDir\\n\\nThe `getGitCommonDir` function (lines 407-445) calls `git rev-parse --git-common-dir` and caches the result. The cache is per working directory, with `ClearGitCommonDirCache()` for tests.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go`\\n\\n**Full content provided above (66 lines).**\\n\\nKey type definitions:\\n- **`SessionState = session.State`** -- type alias\\n- **`PromptAttribution = session.PromptAttribution`** -- type alias\\n- **`CheckpointInfo`** -- checkpoint metadata stored on sessions branch (ID, session ID, created at, files touched, agent, etc.)\\n- **`Condens