shadowBranchName),\\n   628→\\t)\\n   629→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"76b6d326-ae0f-4623-8cb9-ba96f0da0642\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T19:45:09.068Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand how the Entire CLI installs/enables hooks in a repo, and how to disable them. The goal is to write a performance test that:\\n1. Clones a real repo\\n2. Creates a commit WITHOUT Entire hooks (control baseline)\\n3. Enables Entire hooks, creates a commit WITH hooks (test measurement)\\n\\nFind and read:\\n1. How `entire enable` installs hooks - what files does it create/modify? Look in `cmd/entire/cli/commands/` for the enable command\\n2. How hooks are invoked - look at the hook scripts in `.git/hooks/` or wherever they get installed\\n3. How to programmatically call PrepareCommitMsg and PostCommit from Go test code (we already know ManualCommitStrategy has these methods)\\n4. What `.entire/settings.json` needs to contain for hooks to work\\n5. How `entire disable` or cleanup works\\n\\nAlso find:\\n6. The `entire enable` command implementation to understand what setup steps are needed\\n7. Look at how existing integration tests set up Entire in a repo (check `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/`)\\n\\nProvide full file paths and key function signatures.\",\"agentId\":\"aec36e794af2f6ab2\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_011FTUqL5nz1fiMoAaMyjPDn\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Vsij8P3mFaefaMv15QpaUb\",\"uuid\":\"fc2c5ddc-b279-4496-99d5-7d25e0017d5b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T19:45:09.728Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"fc2c5ddc-b279-4496-99d5-7d25e0017d5b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"20bfcd4a-f133-4981-8712-228da5357d19\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"sessionPruning\",\"slug\":\"clever-leaping-stream\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T19:45:09.728Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"i