hould show linear scaling with session count, confirming the O(N) bottleneck in `listAllSessionStates` (reads all session files + checks shadow branch refs) and `filterSessionsWithNewContent`/`postCommitProcessSession` (per-session git operations).\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Plan: Commit Hook Performance Test\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nA user with ~95 sessions (88 ended, 6 idle, 1 active) and ~100 checkpoints experienced **25.5s** commit time vs **0.335s** without Entire (v0.4.7). We need a reproducible test that:\\n1. Recreates this exact scenario locally (no remote/GitHub needed)\\n2. Measures PrepareCommitMsg + PostCommit separately\\n3. Tests scaling across different session counts (10, 50, 100, 200)\\n\\n## New File\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/commit_hook_perf_test.go`** — build tag `hookperf`\\n\\nRun: `go test -v -run TestCommitHookPerformance -tags hookperf -timeout 10m ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/`\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nFollows the same pattern as the existing `postcommit_bench_test.go` (`benchSetupPostCommitRepo`) but:\\n- Uses a `hookperf` build tag (like `pushperf` in checkpoint package) so it doesn't run in CI\\n- Seeds many more sessions (10-200) with realistic phase distribution\\n- Times both PrepareCommitMsg AND PostCommit (the bench only does PostCommit with 1-3 sessions)\\n- Uses `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1` to simulate the human terminal path (which is the expensive path — calls `filterSessionsWithNewContent`)\\n- Uses `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"` in settings to avoid hanging on the TTY prompt\\n\\n### Seeding Strategy\\n\\n| Phase | Count (100-session scenario) | Shadow Branch? | LastCheckpointID? | Notes |\\n|-------|-----|----------------|-------------------|-------|\\n| ENDED | 88 | No | Yes (set to dummy ID) | Already condensed; triggers `repo.Reference()` lookup that fails |\\n| IDLE | 11 | Yes (via `SaveStep`) | No | Have uncommitted checkpoint data on shadow branch |\\n| ACTIVE | 1 | Yes (via `SaveStep`) | No | Has live transcript file + shadow branch |\\n\\nAll sessions share the same `WorktreePath` and `BaseCommit` (matching real scenario).\\n\\n### Test Flow Per Scenario\\n\\n1. `initHookPerfRepo` — git init + initial commit (reuses pattern from `benchSetupPostCommitRepo`)\\n2. `createHookPerfSettings` — write `.entire/settings.json` with `commit_linking: \\\"always\\\"`\\n3. `seedHookPerfSessions` — create session state files + shadow branches:\\n   - ENDED: write state JSON files with `LastCheckpointID` set\\n   - IDLE: use `SaveStep` to create shadow branch checkpoint + state (reuses `benchSetupPostCommitRepo` pattern)\\n   - ACTIVE: use `SaveStep` + create live transcript file\\n4. Stage a file change\\n5. **Time PrepareCommitMsg** — write temp commit message file, call `s.PrepareCommitMsg(ctx, file, \\\"message\\\")`\\n6. Create actual commit with the trailer (so PostCommit finds it)\\n7. **Time PostCommit** — call `s.PostCommit(ctx)`\\n8. Log results + summary table\\n\\n### Key Design Decisions\\n\\n- **No `t.Parallel()`** — required because we use `t.Chdir()` / `t.Setenv()` (same as existing strategy tests)\\n- **Fresh `ManualCommitStrategy{}` for each hook** — matches production where each hook is a separate process\\n- **Clear `paths.ClearWorktreeRootCache()` + `session.ClearGitCommonDirCache()`** before timing — captures full cost including cache misses\\n\\n### Reused Existing Code\\n\\n- `benchSetupPostCommitRepo` pattern from `postcommit_bench_test.go:70` — repo init, git config, SaveStep flow\\n- `session.NewStateStoreWithDir()` from `session/state.go:247` — direct state file creation\\n- `id.MustCheckpointID()` from `checkpoint/id/id.go:44` — create dummy checkpoint IDs for ended sessions\\n- `ManualCommitStrategy.SaveStep()` — creates shadow branches properly\\n\\n### Expected Output\\n\\n```\\n=== 100sessions ===\\n  Sessions:         100 (ended=88, idle=11, active=1)\\n  Setup:            1.2s\\n  PrepareCommitMsg: 8.5s\\n  PostCommit:       15.2s\\n  TOTAL HOOKS:      23.7s\\n\\n========== COMMIT HOOK PERFORMANCE SUMMARY ==========\\nScenario             | Sessions | Prepare      | PostCommit   | TOTAL\\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n10sessions           |       10 |       200ms  |       800ms  |      1000ms\\n50sessions           |       50 |      3500ms  |      8000ms  |     11500ms\\n100sessions          |      100 |      8500ms  |     15200ms  |     23700ms\\n200sessions          |      200 |     17000ms  |     30000ms  |     47000ms\\n```\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\ngo test -v -run TestCommitHookPerformance -tags hookperf -timeout 10m ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/\\n```\\n\\nThe test should show linear scaling with session count, confirming the O(N) bottleneck in `listAllSessionStates` (reads all session files + checks shadow branch refs) and `filterSessionsWithNewContent`/`postCommitProcessSession` (per-session git operations).\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"4fa25fdb-68b5-42d5-8bf3-5137be0734c0\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d9523445-84e5-4de3-a0bb-5f56eb041e1e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"20bfcd4a-f133-4981-8712-228da5357d19\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"sessionPruning\",\"slug\":\"clever-leaping-stream\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01D21G2fHNUxkQdWHLVvpeBv\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01NQYraomKGzRNMAhf7BStRg\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"allowedPrompts\":[{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"run go tests with hookperf tag\"},{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"run git commands in test repos\"},{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"list and read session state files\"},{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"compile Go code\"}],\"plan\":\"# Plan: Realistic Commit Hook Performance Test\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nA user with ~95 sessions experienced 25.5s commit time vs 0.335s without Entire. Our current perf test onl